# Obsidian Integration Config (Example)

<!--
Copy this file to `.claude/state/obsidian-config.md` and fill it in if you want the
`/checkpoint` and `/obsidian-digest-sync` skills to read/write your Obsidian vault.
This file is gitignored by design — your vault paths and project mappings stay local.

If this file does not exist at `.claude/state/obsidian-config.md`, the skills skip the
Obsidian integration silently and only update memory + SESSION_REPORT + research_journal.

Requirements:
- An Obsidian MCP server connected so Claude can read/write vault notes.
  Recommended: mcpvault — a filesystem server that needs NO Obsidian app and NO
  community plugins (https://github.com/bitbonsai/mcpvault). Register it in .mcp.json:
      "obsidian-files": {
        "command": "npx",
        "args": ["-y", "@bitbonsai/mcpvault@latest", "/absolute/path/to/your/vault"]
      }
  The skills call its tools: read_note, write_note (mode overwrite/append), search_notes,
  list_all_tags, list_directory.
- Optional (only for live-app features such as running Obsidian commands or opening
  files): a Local REST API plugin-based server, e.g.
  https://github.com/MarkusPfundstein/mcp-obsidian — this one requires the Obsidian
  desktop app to be open and is NOT needed for the /checkpoint or digest workflows.
-->

## Vault Path

**Absolute path to your Obsidian vault root:**

```
[e.g., /Users/you/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/Obsidian/Research]
```

---

## Vault Structure

<!-- What file/folder does each role live in? -->

| Role | Path inside vault |
|------|-------------------|
| Vault config | [e.g., `_vault-config.md`] |
| Dashboard / Home | [e.g., `Home.md`] |
| Project notes root | [e.g., `Projects/`] |
| Daily journal root | [e.g., `Journal/`] |
| Daily journal filename format | [e.g., `YYYY-MM-DD.md`] |

### Knowledge-base folders (used by `/obsidian-digest-sync`)

<!-- Where the digest-sync skill files concepts, datasets, ideas, and weekly notes.
     Defaults shown; adjust to your vault's layout. -->

| Role | Path inside vault |
|------|-------------------|
| Concepts | [e.g., `concepts/`] |
| Datasets | [e.g., `datasets/`] |
| Ideas | [e.g., `ideas/`] |
| Weekly digests | [e.g., `weekly/`] |

---

## Project-Name Mapping

<!-- Map the working-directory name to the Obsidian project note. /checkpoint uses this to
     find the right project note to update. -->

| Working Directory | Obsidian Project Note |
|-------------------|----------------------|
| [e.g., `bad_controls`] | [e.g., `Projects/Bad Controls.md`] |
| [e.g., `clo-author`] | [e.g., `Projects/clo-author.md`] |

If a working directory has no mapping, /checkpoint will ask the user which project note to use (or to add it).

---

## Category Tags (optional)

<!-- If your dashboard groups projects by category, what category is this one? -->

**Category for this project:** [e.g., Research / Methods / Software]

---

## Notes for /checkpoint

<!-- Any project-specific overrides. -->

- [e.g., Don't update the General Kanban for this project]
- [e.g., Journal entries go under a custom heading "## Dev Log" instead of "## Journal"]
